<recipe>
  <name>Buttermilk Barbecued Turkey Legs</name>
  <safe_name>Buttermilk_Barbecued_Turkey_Legs</safe_name>
  <yield_count>4</yield_count>
  <yield_measure>servings</yield_measure>
  <notes>I'm kind of at a loss to say what the buttermilk soak buys you, especially herbing it when you're likely to put a giant flavor bomb in the manner of BBQ sauce on it.  It'd be good to do a benchmark against a naked 'stick and see how it compares.  Otherwise, not one of the more interesting ways to cook with buttermilk.</notes>
  <prep_time></prep_time>
  <ingredients>
    <ingredient>
      <quantity>4</quantity>
      <ingredient_name>turkey drumsticks</ingredient_name>
      <preparation>14-16oz each</preparation>
    </ingredient>
    <ingredient>
      <quantity>1/2 cup</quantity>
      <ingredient_name>BBQ sauce</ingredient_name>
      <preparation></preparation>
    </ingredient>
    <ingredient>
      <quantity></quantity>
      <ingredient_name>**Marinade</ingredient_name>
      <preparation></preparation>
    </ingredient>
    <ingredient>
      <quantity>2 cups</quantity>
      <ingredient_name>buttermilk</ingredient_name>
      <preparation></preparation>
    </ingredient>
    <ingredient>
      <quantity>2 Tbl</quantity>
      <ingredient_name>dijon mustard</ingredient_name>
      <preparation></preparation>
    </ingredient>
    <ingredient>
      <quantity>2 Tbl</quantity>
      <ingredient_name>honey</ingredient_name>
      <preparation></preparation>
    </ingredient>
    <ingredient>
      <quantity>2 Tbl</quantity>
      <ingredient_name>finely chopped fresh rosemary</ingredient_name>
      <preparation></preparation>
    </ingredient>
    <ingredient>
      <quantity>2 tsp</quantity>
      <ingredient_name>kosher salt</ingredient_name>
      <preparation></preparation>
    </ingredient>
    <ingredient>
      <quantity>1 tsp</quantity>
      <ingredient_name>dried thyme</ingredient_name>
      <preparation></preparation>
    </ingredient>
    <ingredient>
      <quantity>1 tsp</quantity>
      <ingredient_name>dried sage</ingredient_name>
      <preparation></preparation>
    </ingredient>
    <ingredient>
      <quantity>1 tsp</quantity>
      <ingredient_name>dried marjoram</ingredient_name>
      <preparation></preparation>
    </ingredient>
    <ingredient>
      <quantity>1 tsp</quantity>
      <ingredient_name>freshly ground black pepper</ingredient_name>
      <preparation></preparation>
    </ingredient>
  </ingredients>
  <preparation>Combine marinde ingrediens and bag marinde the drumsticks for 3-4 hours in the refrigerator.  Wipe excess marinade off the legs before grilling over indirect medium head until the internal temperature reaches 180F and the juices run clear: about 1 1/2-2 hours. Turn every 30 minutes during cooking process.  Brush occasionally with the BBQ sauce in the last 15-20 minutes.</preparation>
